iness polling.\n+\n+### Task 8: Fix oldest-first ordering in `TransportPool<HttpTarget>`\n+\n+**Files:**\n+- Modify: `crates/reme-transport/src/pool.rs`\n+- Modify: `crates/reme-core/tests/integration.rs`\n+\n+- [ ] **Step 1: Add failing ordering tests for the pool aggregation layer**\n+\n+Cover:\n+- a single target returning oldest-first pages stays oldest-first after aggregation\n+- multi-target deduplication does not return arbitrary order after `HashMap::into_values()`\n+\n+- [ ] **Step 2: Replace arbitrary-order aggregation**\n+\n+Current `HashMap<MessageID, OuterEnvelope>` + `into_values()` is not acceptable for an oldest-first contract.\n+\n+Implement one of:\n+- collect first-seen order in a `Vec` plus a `HashSet<MessageID>`\n+- or use an ordered map keyed by the first-seen sequence\n+\n+Requirement:\n+- preserve deterministic oldest-first order of the aggregated result\n+- do not let deduplication destroy ordering\n+\n+- [ ] **Step 3: Re-run focused transport tests**\n+\n+Run:\n+\n+```bash\n+cargo test -p reme-transport http\n+cargo test -p reme-transport pool\n+```\n+\n+- [ ] **Step 4: Commit the transport changes**\n+\n+```bash\n+git add crates/reme-transport/src/http.rs crates/reme-transport/src/http_target.rs crates/reme-transport/src/pool.rs\n+git commit -m \"feat(transport): drain paginated mailbox fetches\"\n+```\n+\n+## Chunk 5: End-to-End Regression Coverage\n+\n+### Task 9: Add end-to-end coverage for multi-page mailbox drain\n+\n+**Files:**\n+- Modify: `crates/reme-core/tests/integration.rs`\n+\n+- [ ] **Step 1: Add an integration test that exceeds one fetch page**\n+\n+Scenario:\n+- enqueue more than one page worth of messages\n+- fetch through the real HTTP transport path\n+- verify all messages are eventually retrieved exactly once\n+\n+- [ ] **Step 2: Assert oldest-first drain**\n+\n+Verify:\n+- first returned message is the oldest enqueued message\n+- later pages continue in insertion order\n+\n+- [ ] **Step 3: Assert bounded responses indirectly through page count**\n+\n+The integration does not need to inspect HTTP bytes directly if endpoint tests already do, but it must prove:\n+- multi-page retrieval works\n+- no messages are skipped or duplicated\n+\n+- [ ] **Step 4: Use polling instead of fixed sleeps**\n+\n+If the test waits for a server or replicated state, use bounded readiness polling. Do not add new fixed waits.\n+\n+- [ ] **Step 5: Run the focused integration test**\n+\n+Run:\n+\n+```bash\n+cargo test -p reme-core --test integration\n+```\n+\n+## Chunk 6: Full Verification\n+\n+### Task 10: Run the full verification gate\n+\n+**Files:**\n+- Modify: none expected\n+\n+- [ ] **Step 1: Check formatting**\n+\n+```bash\n+cargo fmt --all -- --check\n+```\n+\n+- [ ] **Step 2: Run strict clippy**\n+\n+```bash\n+cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings\n+```\n+\n+- [ ] **Step 3: Run the full test suite**\n+\n+```bash\n+cargo test --workspace\n+```\n+\n+- [ ] **Step 4: Review the diff for scope creep**\n+\n+Confirm:\n+- no backward-compatibility shims were added\n+- no `#71` dedup redesign leaked into this branch\n+- no new fixed-sleep test helpers were introduced\n+\n+- [ ] **Step 5: Final commit if verification fixes were needed**\n+\n+```bash\n+git add <files>\n+git commit -m \"test: cover paginated mailbox fetch end to end\"\n+```\n+\n+## Notes for Implementers\n+\n+- Backward compatibility with old nodes/clients is intentionally out of scope for this MVP/PoC.\n+- Oldest-first means server-owned insertion order, not sender timestamps.\n+- Cursor semantics must be locked at the mailbox-store layer before touching the HTTP contract.\n+- The response-size DoS is not actually solved unless the node enforces a byte budget in addition to a page-size count.\n+- Head-of-line blocking from undecryptable but valid messages is a separate problem and should not be mixed into `#67`.\n+\n+## Suggested Review Checklist\n+\n+- Cursor contract uses mailbox row `id` only\n+- Invalid-row