ool,\n    can_best_effort_store: bool,\n    can_fetch: bool,\n    can_replicate: bool,\n    grants_quorum_credit: bool,\n}\n```\n\nAnd the important invariant is:\n\n- `UntrustedDiscovered` => only `can_best_effort_store = true`\n- everything else false\n\nIf you violate that invariant, you’re implicitly treating anonymous LAN strangers as trusted infrastructure, which is the wrong security model.\n\n<oai-mem-citation>\n<citation_entries>\nMEMORY.md:34-37|note=[memory was used earlier this turn for evidence-first workflow and persisted gh escalation guidance]\n</citation_entries>\n<rollout_ids>\n019ce97a-6c25-7f90-aceb-65ed26af2b2a\n</rollout_ids>\n</oai-mem-citation>",
